      The CEO of Goldman Sachs is no longer a DJ
   =20
 =20

For a while   there seemed to be a small but real and hilarious chance that=
 David Solomon, the chief executive officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc.,
  [1]
 who is also a DJ, might lose his job, as CEO of Goldman Sachs, because he =
is a DJ. The  New York Times reported on the  conflicts of interest arising=
 from Solomon=E2=80=99s CEOing and DJing, somehow. The  Wall Street Journal=
 reported on Goldman partners plotting=C2=A0mutinies, =E2=80=9Csaying it wa=
sn=E2=80=99t a good look for the CEO of one of Wall Street=E2=80=99s most f=
ormidable firms [to also be a DJ].=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
And now  the Financial Times reports that, in fact, Solomon has resolved th=
ese conflicts by stepping down from his job. As a DJ. He=E2=80=99s still=C2=
=A0the CEO of Goldman Sachs. But not also a DJ:

Goldman Sachs chief executive David Solomon has decided to stop DJing at hi=
gh-profile events following criticism that his hobby created a distraction =
from his work leading the Wall Street firm, according to people with knowle=
dge of the decision.=C2=A0
What started as a colourful side hustle that softened Solomon=E2=80=99s pub=
lic image became a lightning rod for criticism of him inside Goldman from b=
ankers disgruntled over strategic mis-steps and lower pay.=C2=A0
Solomon, 61, made the decision to pull back from DJing about a year ago bec=
ause it generated unwanted media attention, the people said.=C2=A0
The last notable event where Solomon DJed was in July 2022 at Lollapalooza,=
 a four-day music festival in Chicago.=C2=A0
Following a request for comment, Goldman spokesman Tony Fratto said: =E2=80=
=9CThis is not news. David hasn=E2=80=99t publicly DJed an event in well ov=
er a year, which we have confirmed multiple times in the past.=E2=80=9D=C2=
=A0

Does he still DJ birthday parties? Client meetings? Are there secret underg=
round clubs deep in Bushwick throwing 3 a.m. raves where David Solomon DJs =
to a small but enthusiastic crowd of electonic-music cognoscenti? No.=C2=A0=
Anyway I am going to forget about this immediately and continue to tell eve=
ryone that the CEO of Goldman Sachs is also a DJ.

