om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">The CEO of Goldman Sachs is no longer a DJ</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For a while <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/33057398.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9v=
cGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMTMvbmFrZWQtc2hvcnQtc2VsbGVyLWdldHMtaW4tdHJ=
vdWJsZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDE3MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3=
VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzEwMTcmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB27cc9d9d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  there seemed</a> to be a small =
but real and hilarious chance that David Solomon, the chief executive offic=
er of Goldman Sachs Group Inc.,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnot=
e-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !imp=
ortant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a> who is also a DJ, might lose his job, as CEO of Goldman Sachs, because=
 he is a DJ. The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
3057398.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMy8wMi8wNS9idXNpbmVzcy9k=
YXZpZC1zb2xvbW9uLWRqLWdvbGRtYW4tc2FjaHMuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfb3=
849b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> New York Times</a> reported on the <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33057398.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy=
5jb20vMjAyMy8wMi8wNS9idXNpbmVzcy9kYXZpZC1zb2xvbW9uLWRqLWdvbGRtYW4tc2FjaHMua=
HRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCfb3849b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> conflicts of interest</=
a> arising from Solomon=E2=80=99s CEOing and DJing, somehow. The <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33057398.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9nb2xkbWFuLXNhY2hzLWNlby1kYXZpZC1zb2xvbW9uLWRqLWJ=
vbnVzZXMtMWE0N2RiZjU_bW9kPWhwX2xlYWRfcG9zNQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6a7bb9=
38" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> Wall Street Journal</a> reported on Goldman partners plotting=
=C2=A0mutinies, =E2=80=9Csaying it wasn=E2=80=99t a good look for the CEO o=
f one of Wall Street=E2=80=99s most formidable firms [to also be a DJ].=E2=
=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And now <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/33057398.256428/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvZDEx=
NjAxYjUtZmJhMS00NjAzLWFjYWQtZWIyZWU1ODdhOGUz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB842cc=
6c3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> the Financial Times reports</a> that, in fact, Solomon has re=
solved these conflicts by stepping down from his job. As a DJ. He=E2=80=99s=
 still=C2=A0the CEO of Goldman Sachs. But not also a DJ:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Goldman Sachs chief executive David Solomon ha=
s decided to stop DJing at high-profile events following criticism that his=
 hobby created a distraction from his work leading the Wall Street firm, ac=
cording to people with knowledge of the decision.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What started as a colourful side hustle that s=
oftened Solomon=E2=80=99s public image became a lightning rod for criticism=
 of him inside Goldman from bankers disgruntled over strategic mis-steps an=
d lower pay.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Solomon, 61, made the decision to pull back fr=
om DJing about a year ago because it generated unwanted media attention, th=
e people said.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The last notable event where Solomon DJed was =
in July 2022 at Lollapalooza, a four-day music festival in Chicago.=C2=A0</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Following a request for comment, Goldman spoke=
sman Tony Fratto said: =E2=80=9CThis is not news. David hasn=E2=80=99t publ=
icly DJed an event in well over a year, which we have confirmed multiple ti=
mes in the past.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Does he still DJ birthday parties? Client meet=
ings? Are there secret underground clubs deep in Bushwick throwing 3 a.m. r=
aves where David Solomon DJs to a small but enthusiastic crowd of electonic=
-music cognoscenti? No.=C2=A0Anyway I am going to forget about this immedia=
tely and continue to tell everyone that the CEO of Goldman Sachs is also a =
DJ.</p>
